sub_title: Looking for job opportunities in the international water sector
summary:
I am interested in everything that has to do with water. 
Throughout my career, I have delved into various water-related subjects, encompassing both technical and soft aspects. For example, I worked in drinking and wastewater technology, on drinking water supply and distribution both in Europe and Africa, as well as on water operator partnerships. I have a PhD for which I studied the biodegradation of hydrocarbons in groundwater at a complex contaminated field site. 

Within all these jobs, what I enjoy the most is combining my scientific capacities with my strong writing and communication skills. Having primarily worked in an international context, I thrive on adventure and learning about different cultures, people and languages. Previous experiences have cultured my flexibility, independence, cultural awareness and the ability to approach tasks in a targeted and creative way. 

Currently, I am exploring opportunities within the environmental/water sector where I can apply my broad skill set in an international context and make meaningful impact.
